


__________________virtual environment:________________________

1. Install venv:
	$ pip install virtualenv / $ pip install --user virtualenv

2. Create a dir:
	$ virtualenv venv
	$ python -m venv venv
3. Activate venv:
	$ source venv/Scripts/activate

4. install django in this venv:(install packages)
	$ pip install django
	$ pip install pandas

4. Create a txt file which contains all necessary packages:
	requirements.txt
5.install all packages from requirements.txt:
	$ pip install -r requirements.txt


6.To show venv:
	$ pip show virtualenv
***version numbers for the installed packages.
	$ pip freeze
	$ pip list
w virtualenv
7. To Check venv version:
	$ pip virtualenv --version
8. Uninstall:
	$ pip uninstall virtualenv 
9. Deactivate:
	$ deactivate
